## Source of Truth

Before ANY change, read:

1. `/docs/features/isp-regulations-panel.md`
2. `/docs/features/_overview.md`

Consult `Logic.md` (left panel routing, spotlight, recommendations, transitions).

## Reusable Components

From `/docs/features/isp-regulations-panel.md` — Dependencies on Shared Code:

| Path | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `src/app/components/layerData.ts` | `layerMeta`, tiers, recommendations, spotlight-related helpers |
| `src/app/components/flagComponents.tsx` | `getFlagForCountry` |
| `src/app/components/CountryBrowser.tsx` | `CountryBrowser`, `CountryRow` |
| `src/app/components/CountryDetailView.tsx` | Country analysis sub-view |
| `src/imports/RightVpnFeatures.tsx` | `MapLayerOption` |
| `src/imports/ProtonPrivacyScore.tsx`, `SurveillanceAlliances.tsx`, `IspRegulations.tsx`, `Identity.tsx`, `P2P.tsx` | Layer icons |

If a shared component covers 80%+ of the requirement, extend it via props/config. Do NOT fork it. Do NOT create a parallel version.

## Feature-Specific Constraints

- Spotlight and risk UI depend on `MapLayerOption` × `LayerTier` — see `layerMeta` and `spotlightDescription` patterns in source.
- Motion/transition behavior is part of UX contract (`Logic.md`).

## Patterns to Follow

- Local state for internal tabs/expanders; global selection via props from `App`.
- Use `AnimatePresence` / `motion` consistently with existing sections.

## What NOT to Do

- Do NOT duplicate `CountryBrowser` / `CountryDetailView` or layer helpers — import from `src/app/components/`.
- Do NOT modify files outside this feature’s scope without approval; coordinated changes need updates to `application-shell.md` and `world-map.md` if props change.
- Do NOT add URL routes.
- Do NOT change layer tier keys or recommendation rules without updating `/docs/features/isp-regulations-panel.md` and `layerData.ts` (see `shared-policies.mdc`).
